    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-10T16:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-10T16:30:00-05:00" n="853"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d853">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856B.01/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scott</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Curaçao</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-10T17:00:00-04:30"
                            >May 10, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>60. The Minister for Foreign Affairs has read me a note which has just been
                    handed him by the Dutch Chargé d’Affaires ad interim and which in close
                    paraphrase is as follows:</p>
                <p>[Here follow two paragraphs similar to the second and third paragraphs of the
                    note of May 10 from the Netherland Minister, printed on <ref target="#pg_731"
                        >page 731</ref>.]</p>
                <p>The Minister then stated that he had just received a telegram from Washington
                    that Curaçao was being reinforced by British troops from Jamaica. He expressed
                    great concern over this development stating that once the British were in it
                    would be difficult to get them to leave after the liquidation of the war. He
                    stated that his Government was very desirous (to fix?) define [<hi rend="italic"
                        >sic</hi>] some line of action immediately and in accord with the United
                    States. For this purpose he was sending a <pb facs="0742" n="733"
                        xml:id="pg_733"/> telegram to the Venezuelan Chargé d’Affaires in Washington
                    to discuss this at once with the Department. He added that the status of Curaçao
                    and Aruba was to be discussed in Cabinet meeting with the President this
                    afternoon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scott</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
